<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>get someone in wrong • get someone wrong</xh5><p> <i>get someone in wrong—</i>cause a person to fall into disfavor with smb.: You’ll <u>get him in wrong</u> with his boss if you keep calling him at the office.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>put someone in the wrong</b>—<i>show a person to be wrong:</i> People want to think that they’re right, and if you <u>put them in the wrong</u>, they won’t like it.</p><p> <i>get someone wrong—</i>misinterpret the intention of smb.’s statement or deed: Don’t <u>get her wrong</u>, she still loves him, but she is understandably cautious.</p></entry>
